1. How to display the first and last column of each line on the terminal using AWK?
We can use the following command-
Syntax: awk ‘{print $1, $NF}’ <filename>
ex: In the below example, I wanted to display only the 1st and last column from “qwert.txt”  file, so I used
awk '{print $1, $NF}' qwert.txt
 






2. How to display the line number followed by last column content of a file using AWK?
We can use the following command-
Syntax: awk '{print NR, $NF}' <filename>
ex: In the below example, I wanted to display the last column with line numbers, so I used 
	awk '{print NR, $NF}' qwert.txt
 

3. What does awk '{print NR,$0}' <file-name> command will do?
This displays all the columns present in the file also the no. of lines in a sequence
 



